race.comment: The well-related VOVO (12) (half to G3 winner Run Harry Run) returned in sparkling fashion with an eight length romp at the Sunny Coast before just running into a couple better at Doomben last time out. Looks the runner in this field with the most upside and can return to winning ways. WAKU WAKU (13) has hit the frame in both runs this campaign and will be ready to peak now third-up from the spell. Solid top-three contender. IRAMA (3) also hails from a handy family (half to G2 winner Serasana) and gets some weight off from the favourable draw. In the mix. LIVALITTLE (14) hasn't been too far away in both runs since the break and may earn some minor money.
